[@Cucumber#Plant*] ([$Cucumis sativus L.#Plant*]) and [$melon#Plant*] ([$C.melo L.#Plant*]) are globally important [$crop#Plant*] species in the family [$cucurbit#Plant*].
However, pests and disease, including various viral diseases, affect [$cucumber#Plant*] and [$melon#Plant*] production in Japan.
Choosing a resistant cultivar is one of the most effective methods for disease control.
Many sources of viral resistance have been identified in [$cucurbits#Plant*], and various resistant commercial cultivars have been bred.
This review describes the present status of [$cucurbit #Plant*]breeding and sources of resistance to the four major viruses in Japan.
